body:
@nikomatsakis For options 3 and 4, when is the error for bivariant lifetime parameters being reported?  Is it an error to _declare_ a bivariant parameter?  Is it merely an error to _instantiate_ a bivariant parameter?

It is not clear to me what the value is of having an explicit syntax for an erroneous construct.

Update from IRC: niko clarified that the error would be (I think) from _inferring_ bivariant lifetime parameter.  But an explicitly specified bivariant parameter would be allowed.
